PLib 6.1.4
Documentation instructions at the bottom.
-------------------------
PLib is a C library made to make parsing command line arguments easier.
The Latest version of plib uses zero memory allocation and is a completely
header-only library which makes compilation a breeze.

Features:
- Header only library 
- Just over 300 lines of code.
- Completly static allocation.
- Optimized for user control.
- Very simple usage and installation.
- Extensive Error handling

--------------------------
Quickstart: 
You only require the plib6.h file which you can download like so:

Edge:
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/x3hy/plib/refs/heads/main/plib6.h

Stable:
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/x3hy/plib/refs/tags/6.1.4/plib6.h
--------------------------
check out example.c for a quickstart!
view the wiki for the full documentation.

